      "description": "Model is applicable to Newtonian blood-analog fluids in turbulent centrifugal pump flows at hematocrit 40±5%, pump speeds 2400–3600 RPM, and flow rates 3–6 L/min. Model is not applicable to pulsatile inflow conditions, non-Newtonian rheology regimes (hematocrit outside 35–45%), or pump geometries with tip clearance deviating more than 15% from the FDA generic pump reference geometry."
    },
